Hey guys, I was waiting to release the source to my recent project until it was fully commented. Turns out, I get bored with commenting! So, some is commented, some is not. I'm just ready to move on to the next project, so here this is.<br /><br />It is a recreation of the Snail Maze Game from the Sega Master System. I think I got pretty close to how the game plays on the SMS. It's a simple game, afterall. Here is the source:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://slydogstudios.org/wp-content/uploads/snail_maze.zip">http://slydogstudios.org/wp-content/upl ... l_maze.zip</a><!-- m --><br /><br />For more info on the game itself, here is the page I have set up for it:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://slydogstudios.org/index.php/snail-maze-game/">http://slydogstudios.org/index.php/snail-maze-game/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />EDIT: Updated web protocol to reflect what it should be (ie the certificate for &quot;secure&quot; expired)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=174">Roth</a> — Tue Mar 06, 2012 2:58 pm</p><hr />
